profile:
Growing up, the family business was Property Maintenance and Landscaping. At an early age, Andrew learned what it takes to look after properties and to run a successful service oriented business. To grow his skills, Andrew entered the electrical trade and completed his apprenticeship, becoming a Red Seal Certified electrician. Following his passion, Andrew moved in to a Project Management role for a boutique residential builder, where he further grew to love taking a dream and transforming it into reality. 

Looking to combine his passion with his training, Andrew founded Lanark Management to provide his clients with the ability to both construct beautiful and functional structures, as well as to effectively manage and maintain their assets and rental properties.
